d it is no surprise that there are contradictions in the aesthetics of music or that our judgements about its value are not internally consistent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aElectronic books. 0aMusicxPhilosophy and aesthetics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Reference.2bisacsh1 aSharpe, R.A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358462440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773584624423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773584624/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles